comment._content:
@whatsthatpicture: Thanks for including the LOC images in your timeline! It's interesting to look at the earliest years of photography without the usual boundaries of private and public collections. 

I'll see if we can add to Flickr the oldest surviving portrait photo made in the United States -- an 1839 self-portrait by Robert Cornelius, <a href="http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2004664436/" rel="nofollow">www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2004664436/</a> 

Helena
